(36, 1, '2011-03-25 09:10:14', '2011-03-25 09:10:14', 'DRAFT  Chairman’s Statement\r\n      General  message\r\n        – The meet  our targets\r\n        – Our  previously stated strategies are working for us\r\n\r\n        – Higher  margin from new products and cost improvement programs (CIP)\r\n      TTI  marks quarter century with record operating profit \r\n        TTI marked  its 25th year in strong health with growth across all businesses and  record operating profits.  \r\n        This  performance was supported by strength in new products, continued geographic  expansion and stabilizing economic conditions in the US.\r\n\r\n      Our full  year profit attributable to owners of the company of HK$XXX million was an  increase of xx% over the prior year.   \r\n        Sales  were $27.X billion for the full year, representing a 9% increase over 2009.  Foreign currency translation negatively impacted sales by %. The Group’s  earnings before interest and tax for the year increased % to reach a record  HK$XX billion.\r\n\r\n  Before  charges.. \r\n      TTI  reacted decisively to the recent difficult global economy by maintaining  investment in new products and marketing while aggressively implementing cost cutting  measures. This approach resulted in the Group emerging stronger with a larger  market share, [leadership in multiple categories] as well as expanded sales and  margins.\r\n      Our Core  Power Equipment business had X% growth in the period.  \r\n        Professional  and industrial power tools further entrenched their dominant market positions  with aggressive marketing promotions. Milwaukee  is benefiting from taking its award winning product line-up onto a global  growth platform. In Floor Care and Appliances Hoover’s revival has strong momentum  and is driving sales and profit growth. Major new product re-launches and  expanded channel distribution supported European sales. Penetration of new  markets in Eastern Europe, South America and Asia are gaining momentum and Australia  grew strongly.\r\n  \r\n        The  ability to leverage our increased volume over fixed overheads and ongoing value  engineering of products are key to driving margin expansion (says Milwaukee). This  helped gross margins expand from 31.3% to 3x% as we were able to offset materials  inflation, a stronger RMB and rising labor costs. Manufacturing efficiency  improved as production capacity in Germany was transferred to our Dongguan  campus in the period. [detail charges].    \r\n\r\n      The  Group achieved a record earnings before interest and tax which increased by X  to X million.  Greater volume is driving  efficiency gains and allowed SG&A costs to be leveraged. SG&A expenses  fell from X% of sales to X sales in the previous period.  We continue to manage a structural reduction  in working capital as global demand planning for inventory is introduced across  our factories and distribution centers. \r\n      During  the period the aggregate amount of US$X million of Convertible Bonds were  converted expanding our share capital by X%. Our gearing position in 2010  showed an improvement to X% from X% in the same period last year. \r\n      We are pleased to announce the Board is recommending a final  dividend of HKX.X cents per share. Together with the interim dividend of  HKX.00 cents per share, this will give a full-year dividend  of HKX.X cents per share, against HKX.00 cents  per share in 2008, an increase of X%.\r\n       \r\n      Manufacturer to marketing company  (We lead the market with market knowledge)\r\n        The Group continues to be guided  by our four Strategic Drivers of Powerful Brands,  Innovative Products, Exceptional People, and Operational Excellence which has driven TTI’s  transition from a manufacturing company to an innovative company focused on the  consumer.\r\n\r\n      In Professional and Industrial  Power Tools TTI has broadened its focus from housing/home? improvement to  become an integrated supplier of infrastructure and engineering maintenance  solutions. We try not to compete with existing products but produce engineering  solutions that innovate and deliver value and improved performance. Paint  sprayers, tile cutters and automatic palm driver are examples of new products  that shape the market with ground breaking innovation. \r\n      Our technological leadership in  lithium ion batteries continues to be a catalyst for innovation and driving  value for customers. In the US  the Ryobi One +system is now the largest and fastest growing battery platform. (Enhance  end-user productivity)\r\n      In Europe  last year our next generation Ryobi 18V lithium battery products [in hyper  green] power tools were launched and expanded further into outdoor products  which can also utilize the battery platform. This ‘network effect’ drives sales  of new products, accessories, batteries and scale efficiencies. \r\n      In floor  care product improvements continue to drive growth. Hoover products have been re-engineered using  wind tunnel technology and Dirt Devil has added a new range of value driven  products.  Vax in the UK has re-launched incorporating \r\n        Technology  originated by Hoover  and Dirt Devil. In response to consumers prioritizing energy efficiency and  convenience a new range of green products has been launched.   \r\n\r\n      OUTLOOK \r\n      Positive  outlook as brands go global\r\n      The  Group is encouraged by the stabilization in the US market and accelerating pace of  penetration in our international markets.  \r\n      TTI  remains committed to leadership through innovation. The next stage of growth is  to maximize growth through the realization of truly global brands with our portfolio  of best-in-class products. To maintain our leadership position we continue to  seek a better cost base while at the same time strengthening our product and  accessory offerings through our commitment to product innovation and R&D. \r\n      Our cost  controls programs range from integrated management of suppliers to increased  undertaking of Kaizen and Lean initiatives across our manufacturing facilities.  While we recognize rising commodity prices and wage trends represent head  winds, the Group is well positioned to drive productive efficiencies and meet  margin targets as we scale the business. \r\n      We  expect to continue to upgrade existing product lines, expand categories and  develop creative accessories.  Strength in  industrial and professional markets is expected to continue into the year  ahead. \r\n\r\n      Next  Generation Innovation \r\n        Momentum  at Milwaukee in  the year ahead will be supported by the launch of next generation Red Lithium  battery technology that provides greater performance and durability. This is  spearheading the launch of new range of 12 and 18 Volt products and accessories.  Cordless and accessories remain key growth engines. (move this section to the  front – cordless leadership)\r\n      We will  continue to invest in increasing the visibility of our brands. Last year Milwaukee entered into a sport marketing sponsorship with Cain Velasquez who became  the UFC Heavy Weight Champion in 2010. \r\n        (Add  Online marketing)\r\n      Seek to  build new distribution channels.  We are  encouraged by the traction in our international organizations.\r\n      The  company is highly optimistic about its outlook and is confident in its strong  position to grow. \r\n\r\n        The  Group will continue to focus on growth opportunities and expect to step up  efforts to penetrate new markets.  Cash  flow is strong with a healthy balance sheet. Well positioned with our brand  portfolio for organic growth, and also to consider opportunistic growth  opportunities.  \r\n  \r\n        I would  like to thank our Exceptional People for working with creativity and passion to  put TTI in such a strong leadership position. We are now well placed to grow  together.\r\n    Thanks  