(374, 1, '2011-03-31 04:10:21', '2011-03-31 04:10:21', '<strong>Our Commitment to Privacy</strong>\r\nThis Privacy Policy demonstrates our commitment to protect the  privacy of individuals with respect to personal data and is designed to  assist you in understanding our policies and practices in relation to  the collection, use, retention, transfer and access of personal data.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Collection of Personally Identifiable Information</strong>\r\nWhen you visit our web site, we will record your visit only and will  not collect any personally identifiable information (i.e. information  that is associated with you as an individual) from you unless otherwise  stated. Cookies used (if any) in any part of our web site will not be  deployed for collecting personally identifiable information. For your  information, Cookies are small pieces of data that can be stored in  users'' hardwares for the purposes of obtaining configuration information  and analysing users'' viewing habits. They are commonly used to track  your preferences in relation to the subject matter of the web site and  make your online experience easier and more personalized.\r\n\r\nThe personally identifiable information we may collect includes, but  not limited to, your name, gender, age, identity document number,  telephone number, fax number, home address, email address, education  level, occupation etc. Refusal to provide such information may deny you  of access to certain parts of our web site, or may render us unable to  handle any application or request you are making, or may otherwise  defeat the objectives of your visit.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Security</strong>\r\nAll personal data you provide to us is secured on our web site with  restricted access by authorized personnel only. Our online registration  process utilizes encryption/security software for data transmission so  as to protect your data via encrypting it in a secure format to ensure  its privacy is secured from unauthorized access or disclosure,  accidental loss, alteration or destruction.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Use of Personally Identifiable Information Collected.</strong>\r\nBy using our web site, you agree that your personal data provided by  you may be used and retained by us for the following purposes and for  other purposes as shall be agreed between you and us or required by law  from time to time :\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>providing our services and processing your enquiries and feedback;</li>\r\n	<li>marketing of goods and/or services by us, our agents or our  subsidiaries, in relation to the services and marketing of any goods  and/or service by any company within Techtronic Group;</li>\r\n	<li>processing of any benefits arising out of or in connection with the services;</li>\r\n	<li>operation and service surveys;</li>\r\n	<li>providing contacts and business details in response to enquiries and complaints;</li>\r\n	<li>incorporating into our user disclosure;</li>\r\n	<li>auditing;</li>\r\n	<li>enabling us to comply with our obligations to interconnect or other industry practices;</li>\r\n	<li>and other related purposes.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Retention of the Information</strong>\r\nWe retain records of your dealings with us for the above purposes.  Our general policy is to retain the information as long as the data is  still required for the purposes mentioned above.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Sharing and Disclosure of Information</strong>\r\nNormally, we may share your information within Techtronic group of  companies, or transfer it to their respective subsidiaries and  affiliated companies and any company in which the same has an interest  (collectively “Techtronic Group”) in Hong Kong or abroad.\r\n\r\nYou further agree that we may disclose and transfer (whether in Hong  Kong or abroad) to our agents, contractors, any telecommunications  operators, any third party collection agencies, any credit reference  agencies, any security agencies, any credit providers, banks, financial  institutions, any other persons under a duty of confidentiality to us,  any company within Techtronic Group and any of our actual or proposed  assignees or transferees of our rights with respect to you to use,  disclose, hold, process, retain or transfer such personal data for the  purposes mentioned above.\r\n\r\nYou should however note that the privacy protection set out in this  Privacy Policy does not apply to personal data which is passed to third  parties, and we are not responsible for the protection of your personal  data or the lack thereof by such third parties.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Access to and Correction of Information</strong>\r\nUnder the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance, you have the right to:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>check whether we hold any of your personal data;</li>\r\n	<li>access your personal data held by us;</li>\r\n	<li>require us to correct any personal data which is inaccurate;</li>\r\n	<li>ascertain our policies and practices (from time to time) in relation to personal data and the types of personal data held by us.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nWe may charge a reasonable fee for the processing of any personal data  access request. All requests for access to or correction of personal  data or information regarding policies and practices and types of  personal data held should be in writing and addressed to our Personal  Data Privacy Officer.\r\n<strong>Personal Data Privacy Officer\r\nTechtronic Industries Co. Ltd.\r\n24/F, CDW Building\r\n388 Castle Peak Road\r\nTsuen Wan, New Territories</strong>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>Your Consent</strong>\r\nBy using our web site, you consent to our collection and use of your  personal data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.  We will post any  changes to our privacy policy on our web site.  We are not responsible  for the practices employed by websites linked to or from ours nor the  content or information contained therein.\r\n<strong>Copyright © 2008, TTI All rights reserved.</strong>', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'privacy', '', '', '2012-04-15 17:57:11', '2012-04-15 17:57:11', '', 0, 'http://tti.sedgwick-richardson.net/?page_id=374', 0, 'page', '', 0),
